    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-01T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-01T16:00:00-05:00" n="255"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d255">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851D.001/48: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Port-of-Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hall</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-01T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 1, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>117. We understand that the French National Committee has issued instructions to
                    Bertaud to return to London with his wife by first available means. Please take
                    this matter up with General Patch<note n="61" xml:id="d255fn61">Gen. Joseph D.
                        Patch, Commanding Officer, Trinidad Sector and Base Commander, Headquarters
                        of Caribbean Defense Command.</note> and local British authorities with a
                    view to facilitating departure as quickly as possible. It is desired that their
                    return to London be accomplished by means of a route which does not involve
                    transit through the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
